  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Thanks for trying it out. Unfortunately I think removing those will be a breaking change, so not something we will be able to get to for the coming months. For the styling; you can add the hash as it suggested; for `unsafe-eval`, this is likely due to the templating. I don't think it's completely trivial removing or replacing that one though. It's something that will take us at least a few months to get to. Is that okay? For now I'll close this issue, since we found out the things we have are still the same violations as described in #2868",
